article.description: — Isaac Mushila had 27 points and 13 rebounds as Texas A&M-Corpus Christi rolled past Northwestern State 89-67 on Thursday night in a Southland Conference opener for both teams.
article.headline: Mushila lifts Texas A&M-CC over Northwestern State 89-67
article.linkText: Mushila lifts Texas A&M-CC over Northwestern State 89-67
article.story: KATY, Texas -- — Isaac Mushila had 27 points and 13 rebounds as Texas A&M-Corpus Christi rolled past Northwestern State 89-67 on Thursday night in a Southland Conference opener for both teams. Mushila shot 10 for 12 from the floor. De'Lazarus Keys had 12 points for Texas A&M-CC (12-3). Trevian Tennyson added 11 points and Terrion Murdix had seven points, 11 rebounds and six assists. Robert Chougkaz had 14 points for the Demons (3-12). LaTerrance Reed added 12 points and Carvell Teasett had 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
